posts.raw_content:
As I've posted in the past I've been dx with bilateral breast cancer and am refusing chemotherapy. I am taking 2 medications. One is the hormone treatment that blocks estrogen production as estrogen is what is feeding my cancer. The other is a CDK4/6 inhibitor, which works by blocking cyclin-dependent kinases 4 and 6 (CDK4/6), proteins that help regulate cell growth and division, thereby slowing the progression of cancer cells. This second medication is really taking a toll on me physically. It causes major GI upset for which I take other meds to counter those issues. It has also caused a fatigue that I cannot accurately explain. It feels as if I've ran a marathon every single day and it's getting harder for me to actually live a somewhat decent life. I'm at the point I want to quit taking it but I know I have to continue taking it in order to have the best shot at stopping the spread of this cancer and healing it. 

I am also using fenben which anyone that's taken it knows also causes major GI upset. 

It's hard. Everything seems so hard right now and I'm wavering in any kind of resolve to fight tbh. Sometimes I want to just stop it all and let nature run it's course. 

I need prayers for strength to endure please. I need prayers for healing, comfort, patience, and relief from the side effects of these medications. 

Thanks fam.
